# Version Control Rules

## No direct pushes to `main`

All code must enter `main` through a reviewed merge from a dev/feature/fix branch.

## Branch naming

| Type | Prefix | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| New feature | `feature/` | `feature/oauth-integration` |
| Bug fix | `fix/` | `fix/memory-leak-m5` |
| Active development | `dev/` | `dev/api-endpoints` |

## Commit message format

```
type: short description (imperative mood)
```

Examples:
- `feat: add swipe-to-delete gesture to track cards`
- `fix: resolve memory leak in avatar video loader`
- `chore: update dependencies`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `style`
